Enum Class Processor.ProcessorState

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<Processor.ProcessorState>
microsim.simulation.component.Processor.ProcessorState
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<Processor.ProcessorState>, Constable
Enclosing class:
Processor
public static enum Processor.ProcessorState extends Enum<Processor.ProcessorState>
Enum representing all possible states of a processor in its instruction cycle. These can be categorized as follows:
  • Instruction fetch and decode:
    • FETCH.
    • DECODE.
  • Execution states:
    • Movement instructions:MOV, MOV_IMMEDIATE, LOAD, LOAD_POST, LOAD_IMMEDIATE, STORE, STORE_IMMEDIATE.
    • Arithmetic instructions: ADD, ADD_IMMEDIATE, SUB, SUB_IMMEDIATE, CMP, CMP_IMMEDIATE, INC, DEC.
    • Logical instructions: AND, AND_IMMEDIATE, OR, OR_IMMEDIATE, NOT.
    • Utility instructions: SHL, SHL_IMMEDIATE, SHR, SHR_IMMEDIATE.
    • Stack Operations: PUSH, POP, POP_POST, CALL, RET, RET_POST.
    • Jump instructions: JMP_IMMEDIATE, JMP, JO_IMMEDIATE, JO, JS_IMMEDIATE, JS, JZ_IMMEDIATE, JZ, JC_IMMEDIATE, JC.
    • Other instructions: NOP, HLT.
  • Memory access routines:
    • Read: MEM_READ0, MEM_READ1, MEM_READ2
    • Write: MEM_WRITE0, MEM_WRITE1, MEM_WRITE2, MEM_WRITE3
